For pages created with a template, we would like to have a way to apply some kind of format with automatic numbering to the page title. For example, we have a page template for creating a software development standard. To meet our requirement of page title formatting and numbering, we currently have a note that tells people what the title of the previously standard is (e.g., Standard-0456) and then we remind them that the page title of the next standard should be one more than that (e.g., Standard-0457).  The user has to manually enter the entire page title, but it would be nice if we could automatically include the first part of the title (Standard-nnnn), automatically incrementing the nnnn.

