Tables (and possibly other formatting/macros) are failing to render properly when rendered from the children macro. 

To replicate:

# Create a parent page with the following markup:

{noformat}
{excerpt-include:<EXCERPT_NAME>|nopanel=true} <!-- This works perfectly -->

{children:excerpt=true} <!-- This doesn't work -->
{noformat}

# Create a child page with the following markup:

{noformat}
{excerpt:<EXCERPT_NAME>}
|| ABC || DEF ||
| 123 | 456 |
{noformat}
{excerpt}

The raw wiki markup will appear in 3.5.x and earlier, in 4.0 the table headings will appear.

