I just lost a whole page's worth of data because I was creating a new page and tried to save but was only told afterwards that I couldn't save it because my license had expired. I don't know if the expiry happened _as I was writing_ or if it happened before.

The user isn't told when they go into "Create Page" that it won't be able to be saved because their license has expired. This is bad. Then, drafts aren't even saved, so if they submit the form, they've lost everything. Also bad.

Please enhance the user experience here. I know it might be an edge case, but you don't want evaluators having a bad experience.

