When a user shares a page with the Share feature, it generates an email with the From address set to that user's email address. Unfortunately this causes the emails to be blocked as spoofed by our email server. There's currently no way to make the emails come from a different address.

We're using Jira Studio - most of the emails generated come from jira@oursubdomain.jira.com - it'd be fine if the Share emails came from that address too.

In addition, it affects the mention feature .

